            <fr:display-uri>006V</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/lectures/006V/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Verum rule">Verum rule</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>When it comes to verum, things are simpler.
Remember that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top ]]></fr:tex> is meant to mean MAXIMUM TRUE: THE TRUEST THING.
So it should be very <html:em>easy</html:em> to prove.
And indeed it is, via its introduction rule:</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/lectures/ellieripley/" title="Ellie Ripley" uri="https://negation.rocks/lectures/ellieripley/" display-uri="ellieripley" type="local">Ellie Ripley</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>4</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>15</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://negation.rocks/lectures/007F/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>007F</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/lectures/007F/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Verum introduction:">Verum introduction:</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
                  <fr:resource hash="cdb6057c70d96542095ce27641d7c422">
                    <fr:resource-content>
                      <html:img src="/lectures/cdb6057c70d96542095ce27641d7c422.svg" />
                    </fr:resource-content>
                    <fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[
  \usepackage {bussproofs}
  \newcommand {\DP }{\DisplayProof }
  ]]></fr:resource-source>
                    <fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[\AxiomC{\ensuremath{\vphantom{\top }\vphantom{|}}}\LeftLabel{\ensuremath{\scriptsize  \top  I:\quad }}\UnaryInfC{\ensuremath{\top \vphantom{|}}}\DP]]></fr:resource-source>
                  </fr:resource>
                </html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>Note that there is <html:em>nothing</html:em> above the line here; an application of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top  I]]></fr:tex> counts as a proof of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top ]]></fr:tex> from <html:em>no</html:em> assumptions at all.
It's just directly a proof in its own right.
So this rule gives us another way to start a proof, besides assuming a sentence.
(So far, though, those are the only two ways we can begin; all our other rules only build up bigger proofs from already-existing ones.)</html:p>
            <html:p>And just like <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bot ]]></fr:tex> has no introduction rule, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top ]]></fr:tex> has no elimination rule.
The idea is something like this: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top ]]></fr:tex> is just so stinking true that <html:em>knowing</html:em> that it's true gives you no information at all.
Thus, it doesn't allow you to go on to conclude anything in particular.</html:p>
            <html:p>You can still continue a proof past a use of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\top  I]]></fr:tex>; you just have to do it with some other rule.
For example, here is a proof:</html:p>
            <html:p>
              <fr:resource hash="6813bfff492861b280d03a4d5bbe3faf">
                <fr:resource-content>
                  <html:img src="/lectures/6813bfff492861b280d03a4d5bbe3faf.svg" />
                </fr:resource-content>
                <fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[
  \usepackage {bussproofs}
  \newcommand {\DP }{\DisplayProof }
  ]]></fr:resource-source>
                <fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
\AxiomC{\ensuremath{\top  \rightarrow  q\vphantom{|}}}
\AxiomC{\ensuremath{\vphantom{\top }\vphantom{|}}}
\LeftLabel{\ensuremath{\scriptsize  \top  I:\quad }}
\UnaryInfC{\ensuremath{\top \vphantom{|}}}
\LeftLabel{\ensuremath{\scriptsize  \rightarrow  E:\quad }}
\BinaryInfC{\ensuremath{q\vphantom{q \lor  r}\vphantom{|}}}
\LeftLabel{\ensuremath{\scriptsize  \lor  I_r:\quad }}
\UnaryInfC{\ensuremath{\bot  \lor  q\vphantom{|}}}
\DP
]]></fr:resource-source>
              </fr:resource>
            </html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
